{
  "name": "Locus: Ensorcell Cascade",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"item-attunement\"><p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to an already magical item.)</em></p></div><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>This carefully shaped shard of glass was forged in enchanted fires and cooled in the waters of a lake which was said to bleed into the Elemental Plane of Water.</p><p>While attuned, the glass merges magically merges with an <strong>already magical item </strong>of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, requires 10 minutes to complete and it upon completion the item has various glass crystalline structures appear from it. Once completed, the item becomes magical for the purpose of overcoming resistances.</p><p><strong>Effect: </strong>The first time the attuned casts a spell using each spell slot of 1st through 5th; roll a d6. Based on the total rarity of the item this locus is attached to, you may regain the spell slot used if the result is greater than or equal to the result specified in the table below. Each level of spell slot can only benefit from this effect once per long rest.</p><table><thead><tr><td>Rarity</td><td>d6 Result</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Uncommon</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>Rare</td><td>5+</td></tr><tr><td>Very Rare</td><td>5+</td></tr><tr><td>Exceptional</td><td>4+</td></tr><tr><td>Peerless</td><td>4+</td></tr></tbody></table>",
